"data: {"choices":[{"delta":{"content":"The sky is typically **blue** during the day. This happens because of a phenomenon called Rayleigh scattering, where shorter blue wavelengths of sunlight scatter more in Earth's atmosphere than longer red wavelengths.\\n\\nHowever, the sky can appear different colors depending on conditions:\\n- **Red, orange, or pink** at sunrise and sunset\\n- **Gray or white** on cloudy days\\n- **Deep purple or black** at night (when the sun isn't illuminating the atmosphere)\\n- **Other colors** during unusual atmospheric conditions","role":"assistant"},"finish_reason":"stop","index":0}],"id":"msg_vrtx_01GyPUGfsSZFcEtrNApDrsFn","model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","object":"chat.completion.chunk","usage":{"completion_tokens":120,"prompt_tokens":13,"prompt_tokens_details":{"cached_tokens":0},"total_tokens":133}}

